The most important crises for Italy is the war crisis that is going on in the government and the crisis of legitimacy of boring politics in a country that was supposed to be doing so well, but is not anymore.

Almost 27 years ago, on 31 December, exactly, is when Italy started to use the euro as the currency. The collapse of the Lira was a huge event. As for the euro exchange rate, which was around 850 Lira, then it was over 1600, 1800 at one point. The introduction on 1 January, 1999, was the final collapse of the Lira. It went down to 1300 Lira on New Year's night that year.

That's really interesting. In what ways do you think the results of the 1994 elections matter for Italy these days?

Decisions in this country don't take into account the people, they take into account significant groups of interest who can try to work together and certainly leaders don't have many other visions for the country.
